HEADWORD: Pillowed
<hw>Pil"lowed</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Provided with a
pillow or pillows; having the head resting on, or as on, a
pillow.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Pillowed</qex>on buckler cold and hard.</q> <rj><qau>Sir W.
Scott.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pillow lace</ent>⟦br⟧
